<!-- 流行概況 -->
'''西非伊波拉病毒疫症'''，是2013年12月始於[[西非|西非]]，由[[伊波拉病毒|伊波拉病毒]]引發之疾病大流行。此乃[[伊波拉出血熱|伊波拉出血熱]]史上最嚴重的一次爆發，亦為該病首次登陸西非。<ref name=CDC_order/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMp1409903?query=featured_home&|title=Ebola 2014 — New Challenges, New Global Response and Responsibility|publisher=The New England Journal of Medicine|accessdate=2015-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150101234836/http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMp1409903?query=featured_home&|archive-date=2015-01-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>此次疫情錄得的最高[[病死率|臨床致死率]]為<section begin=cfr />71%<section end=cfr /><ref name=":1"/><ref name="WHO2014_12_28">{{cite web |url=http://apps.who.int/ebolaweb/sitreps/20141231/20141231.pdf |title=Ebola response roadmap - Situation report - 31 December 2014 |publisher=World Health organization |date=2014-12-31 |accessdate=2015-01-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231222250/http://apps.who.int/ebolaweb/sitreps/20141231/20141231.pdf |archive-date=2014-12-31 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="cfrebolavirus">{{cite web|url=http://epidemic.bio.ed.ac.uk/ebolavirus_fatality_rate|title=Case Fatality Rate for ebolavirus|publisher=|date=2015|work=Ebola data and statistics|accessdate=2015-01-28|archive-date=2014-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140829075833/http://epidemic.bio.ed.ac.uk/ebolavirus_fatality_rate|dead-url=yes}}</ref>；就診病人的死亡率則為57-59%<ref name="WHOreport">{{cite web |url=http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/situation-reports/en/ |title=Ebola Situation report |publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] |date=12-01-2015 |work=Ebola data and statistics |accessdate=2015-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722020855/http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/situation-reports/en/ |archive-date=2015-07-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。伊波拉出血熱首次於1976年出現在現時的[[剛果|剛果]]及[[南蘇丹|南蘇丹]]，并常於[[撒哈拉以南非洲|非洲撒哈拉以南的地區]]造成間歇性流行。這一次的爆發源於2013年12月的[[畿內亞|畿內亞]]，後散播至[[利比里亞|利比里亞]]及[[塞拉利昂|塞拉利昂]]。<ref name=":1">{{cite web |url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1411100?query=featured_home |title=Ebola Virus Disease in West Africa — The First 9 Months of the Epidemic and Forward Projections |journal=New England Journal of Medicine |date=2014-09-23 |accessdate=2014-09-23 |author=WHO Ebola Response Team |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924041239/http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1411100?query=featured_home |archive-date=2014-09-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[尼日利亞|尼日利亞]]及[[塞內加爾|塞內加爾]]曾出現20人及1人的少数感染個案，但是兩國至今沒有再增添新的病例<ref name=sitrep_7Nov2014>{{cite web |url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/137592/1/roadmapsitrep_7Nov2014_eng.pdf?ua=1 |title=EBOLA RESPONSE ROADMAP SITUATION REPORT UPDATE |publisher=World Health organization |date=07-11-2014 |accessdate=07-11-2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107223607/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/137592/1/roadmapsitrep_7Nov2014_eng.pdf?ua=1 |archive-date=2014-11-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>；[[馬里|馬里]]也曾有數人染病<ref name="health-ebola-mali-idINL6N0T15CN20141112">{{cite web|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2014/11/12/health-ebola-mali-idINL6N0T15CN20141112|title=UPDATE 1-Mali confirms new case of Ebola, locks down Bamako clinic|publisher=|accessdate=2014-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141116031456/http://in.reuters.com/article/2014/11/12/health-ebola-mali-idINL6N0T15CN20141112|archive-date=2014-11-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而[[英國|英國]]也有一名隔離患者<ref name="WHO2014_12_28"/>。[[美國|美國]]與[[西班牙|西班牙]]均出現境外移入個案，患者都是醫護人員，但是病毒沒有進一步擴散。<ref name=El_Mundo>{{cite web|title=Una enfermera que atendió al misionero fallecido García Viejo, contagiada de ébola|url=http://www.elmundo.es/madrid/2014/10/06/5432bb62e2704e347a8b4577.html?a=a733fe5654cd56f5e1d50d769a9b4204&t=1412616936|accessdate=06-10-2014|date=06-10-2014|publisher=El Mundo|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924172642/http://www.elmundo.es/madrid/2014/10/06/5432bb62e2704e347a8b4577.html?a=a733fe5654cd56f5e1d50d769a9b4204&t=1412616936|archive-date=2015-09-24|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Ebola_Outbreak_total_WHO_8_Oct">{{cite web|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/136020/1/roadmapsitrep_8Oct2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|title=WHO: Ebola Outbreak Situation Report|accessdate=2014-10-15|date=08-10-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009022545/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/136020/1/roadmapsitrep_8Oct2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|archive-date=2014-10-09|dead-url=no}}</ref><section begin=casesasof />{{As of|2016|1|14}}<section end=casesasof />，[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]及多國政府共錄得<section begin=cases />28,637<section end=cases />宗感染個案及<section begin=deaths />11,315<section end=deaths />宗死亡案例。<section begin=caserefs /><ref name=WHO2016_1_14>{{cite web|url=http://who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2016/ebola-zero-liberia/en/|title=WHO - Latest Ebola outbreak over in Liberia; West Africa is at zero, but new flare-ups are likely to occur|work=World Health Organization|accessdate=2016-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117002223/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2016/ebola-zero-liberia/en/|archive-date=2016-01-17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Reuters2014_12_16">{{cite web |url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/144498/1/roadmapsitrep_26Nov2014_eng.pdf?ua=1 |title=Mali ends last quarantines, could be Ebola-free next month |publisher=Reuters |date=2014-12-16 |accessdate=2014-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220203650/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/144498/1/roadmapsitrep_26Nov2014_eng.pdf?ua=1 |archive-date=2014-12-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WHO20141022">{{cite web |url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/137091/1/roadmapsitrep22Oct2014_eng.pdf |accessdate=2014-10-22 |title=Ebola Response Roadmap Situation Report |date=2014-10-22 |author=World Health Organization |work= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024225624/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/137091/1/roadmapsitrep22Oct2014_eng.pdf |archive-date=2014-10-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref><section end=caserefs />不過，他們相信這比實際的數字低。<ref name="CDC Estimating future number of cases"/><ref name="Reuters">{{cite web | url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/22/us-health-ebola-who-idUSKCN0IB23220141022 | title=Official WHO Ebola toll near 5,000 with true number nearer 15,000 | publisher=Reuters | date=2014-10-22 | accessdate=2014-10-25 | author=Miles, Tom | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024205537/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/22/us-health-ebola-who-idUSKCN0IB23220141022 | archive-date=2014-10-24 | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="HP New cases 10,000 per week">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/14/who-ebola-cases_n_5982078.html|title=WHO: New Ebola Cases Could Be Up To 10,000 Per Week In 2 Months|date=2014-10-14|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=2014-10-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014220329/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/14/who-ebola-cases_n_5982078.html|archivedate=2014-10-14}}</ref> 

<!-- 疫情影響 -->
這次爆發使伊波拉出血熱首次成為[[流行病|流行病]]。以往的爆發均為局部性，並多於數週內受到控制。造成大規模爆發的原因有很多：社會貧困、醫療體系存有漏洞、人們對政府的不信任及當地政府對疫情上報的延誤均為重要因素；除此，當地的埋葬傳統、爆發地人口稠密和國際間的忽視亦有一定影響。<ref name=sitrep_24Sept2014>{{cite web|title=Ebola Response Roadmap Situation Report|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/134771/1/roadmapsitrep_24Sept2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|publisher=World Heath Organisation|accessdate=2014-09-25|page=6|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928120710/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/134771/1/roadmapsitrep_24Sept2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|archive-date=2014-09-28|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Runaway Doctors and Missing Supplies Cripple Care in Ebola-Hit Liberia|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ebola-virus-outbreak/runaway-doctors-missing-supplies-cripple-care-ebola-hit-liberia-n220686|publisher=NBC news|accessdate=08-10-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008005237/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ebola-virus-outbreak/runaway-doctors-missing-supplies-cripple-care-ebola-hit-liberia-n220686|archive-date=2014-10-08|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Global Post">{{cite web |url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/xinhua-news-agency/140527/8-ebola-suspects-freed-relatives-sierra-leone |title=8 Ebola suspects freed by relatives in Sierra Leone |work=Global Post |date=2014-05-28 |accessdate=2014-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531084044/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/xinhua-news-agency/140527/8-ebola-suspects-freed-relatives-sierra-leone |archive-date=2014-05-31 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Today Health">{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/health/growing-ebola-outbreak-threatens-overwhelm-volunteers-2D79775266|title=Growing Ebola Outbreak Threatens to Overwhelm Volunteers|publisher=Today Health|date=08-06-2014|accessdate=2014-06-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714212443/http://www.today.com/health/growing-ebola-outbreak-threatens-overwhelm-volunteers-2D79775266|archive-date=2014-07-14|dead-url=no}}</ref> 隨著疫症不斷擴散，很多醫院因人手不足或設備不夠而不堪重負。一些醫學家認為，醫院無力處理其他醫療需求很可能額外增加死亡人數。<ref name=":2">{{cite web | url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/ebola-outbreak-deaths-from-malaria-and-other-diseases-could-soar-while-africas-overstretched-healthcare-systems-fight-the-virus-expert-warns-9667362.html | title=Ebola outbreak: Deaths from malaria and other diseases could soar while Africa's over-stretched healthcare systems fight the virus, expert warns | publisher=The Independent | date=2014-10-27 | accessdate=2014-10-28 | author=Cooper, Charlie | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103184339/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/ebola-outbreak-deaths-from-malaria-and-other-diseases-could-soar-while-africas-overstretched-healthcare-systems-fight-the-virus-expert-warns-9667362.html | archive-date=2014-11-03 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Diary">{{cite news|last1=Farmer|first1=Paul|title=Diary|url=http://www.lrb.co.uk/v36/n20/paul-farmer/diary|accessdate=2014-10-25|publisher=London Review of Books|date=2014-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025112045/http://www.lrb.co.uk/v36/n20/paul-farmer/diary|archive-date=2014-10-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>需要接觸患者體液的醫療員工為高危一族，而世衛亦表示，截至8月，有10%的死者為醫護人員。<ref name="As Ebola Outbreak Surges, Health Officials Slam International 'Coalition of Inaction'">{{cite web |url=http://www.commondreams.org/news/2014/09/03/ebola-outbreak-surges-health-officials-slam-international-coalition-inaction |title=As Ebola Outbreak Surges, Health Officials Slam International 'Coalition of Inaction' |publisher=Common Dreams |work=As Ebola Outbreak Surges, Health Officials Slam International 'Coalition of Inaction' |date=03-09-2014 |accessdate=07-09-2014 |author=McCauley, Lauren |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905045701/http://www.commondreams.org/news/2014/09/03/ebola-outbreak-surges-health-officials-slam-international-coalition-inaction |archive-date=2014-09-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>病例分佈不均使一些患者需遠赴其他醫療機構就診，此舉的可行性在很多情況下不大。<ref name="WHO2014_12_10">{{cite web|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/145198/1/roadmapsitrep_10Dec2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|title=Ebola response roadmap - Situation report|publisher=World Health organization|date=10-12-2014|accessdate=11-12-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210214551/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/145198/1/roadmapsitrep_10Dec2014_eng.pdf?ua=1|archive-date=2014-12-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>

